.TH CUT 1
.SH NAME
cut \- cut selected fields or characters from lines
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cut
.B -c
.I list
[
.IR file ...
]
.br
.B cut
.B -f
.I list
[
.B -d
.I delim
] [
.B -s
] [
.IR file ...
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Cut
writes selected fields or character positions from each line
of each
.I file
(default: standard input)
to standard output.
.PP
If the
.B -f
option is given, the selection is by field;
if
.B -c
is given, it is by character position.
.PP
The
.I list
specifies the fields or character positions to select.
It is a comma-separated list of numbers and ranges:
.TP
.I N
Select field or character
.IR N .
.TP
.IB N - M
Select fields or characters
.I N
through
.IR M .
.TP
.IB N -
Select from field or character
.I N
to end of line.
.TP
.BI - M
Select from beginning to field or character
.IR M .
.PP
Fields and characters are numbered from 1.
.PP
The options are:
.TP
.BI -d " delim"
Use
.I delim
as the field delimiter character (default: tab).
Only valid with
.BR -f .
.TP
.B -s
Suppress lines that do not contain the delimiter.
Without
.BR -s ,
lines without the delimiter are passed through unchanged.
Only valid with
.BR -f .
.TP
.B -n
Accepted but ignored.
Inferno is natively UTF-8; character boundaries are always respected.
.SH EXAMPLES
.LP
Print the second field of a colon-separated file:
.IP
.B "cut -d: -f2 /etc/passwd"
.LP
Print characters 1 through 10:
.IP
.B "cut -c1-10 file"
.LP
Print fields 1, 3, and 5 onward:
.IP
.B "cut -f1,3,5- file"
.SH SOURCE
.B /appl/cmd/cut.b
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR awk (1),
.IR tr (1)
